= render "breadcrumbs", active_index: 4

.wizard-intro
  :markdown
    Please add details about an activity your organisation performs. You need to add at least one activity to appear on the map. You will be able to add more later.

    An activity could be of any size. It may be the only thing that your organisation does, or it may be one of a number of activities that you deliver with a number of partners.

= simple_form_for @project, url: [:organisations, :build, :create_project] do |f|
  .field-with-notes
    .notes
      %p Please enter the official title you would give to this activity, i.e. an event name; a research project title etc.
    .field
      = f.input :name, label: 'Name of your activity', input_html: { class: 'project-auto-suggest', autocomplete: :off }
      = render 'suggestions'

  .field-with-notes
    .notes
      %p Describe what your activity is about. Please keep this as brief as possible (no more than a few hundred words).
    .field
      = f.input :description, as: :text

  .field-with-notes
    .notes
      :markdown
        People work on or support DSI in different kinds of ways. How would you best describe this activity?

        We would like to understand what the main focus of your activity is - we realise the list below may not be a perfect fit, but please try to pick the best option possible from the list below.

        If you feel your activity is really different, use the _Other_ option, and tell us a bit about it in a few words.
    .field
      = f.input :activity_type_label, label: 'Type of activity', as: :radio, collection: Concepts::ActivityType.top_level_concepts
      = f.input :activity_type_label_other, label: false, as: :string, placeholder: 'Other - please state', wrapper_html: { class: 'other' }

  .field-with-notes
    .notes
      How would you describe the roles you play in this activity?
    .field
      = f.input :organisation_natures, label: 'Relationship in activity', as: :check_boxes, collection: Concepts::ProjectMembershipNature.all.resources, value_method: :uri, required: true

  .wizard-button-wrapper
    = f.button :submit, 'Next step &raquo;'.html_safe